==Ammaron==
{{for|the Filipino Mythological figure|Ama-ron}}
:''Ammaron should not be confused with [[Amaron]], [[Ammoron]], or [[Amoron]], three other Book of Mormon figures with similar names.''

According to the [[Book of Mormon]], '''Ammaron''' ({{IPAc-en|ˈ|æ|m|ə|r|ɒ|n}};<ref>[http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/pronunciation?lang=eng LDS.org: "Book of Mormon Pronunciation Guide"] (retrieved 2012-02-25), [[Wikipedia:IPA for English|IPA]]-ified from «ăm´a-rän»</ref> '''Ammoron''' a frequent scribal variant in the Printer's Manuscript<ref>R. Skousen, ''Analysis of Textual Variants of the Book of Mormon'' (Provo: FARMS, 2004-2009), 3:1507, 6:3578-80.</ref>) was a [[Nephite]] record-keeper and perhaps a [[prophet]].  He was also one of the authors who wrote on the [[Plates of Nephi]], which Mormon abridged.

Ammaron took custody of the [[Record of the Nephites|Nephite records]] after the death of his brother, [[Amos, son of Amos|Amos]], in AD 306 and three verses contain Mormon's abridgment of his writings.<ref>{{Sourcetext|source=Book of Mormon|version=1981|book=4 Nephi|chapter=1|verse=49}}</ref> In 321, he hid all the Nephites' sacred writings in the [[Hill Shim]] in the [[Land of Antum]]. He later instructed the ten-year-old future prophet [[Mormon (prophet)|Mormon]] to wait until he was 24 and then take the [[Large Plates of Nephi|Plates of Nephi]] from the hill (leaving the other writings hidden) and continue the record.

