The '''Archbishop of Luxembourg''' is the [[Ordinary (officer)|ordinary]] of the [[Roman Catholic Church|Roman Catholic]] [[archbishopric]] of [[Luxembourg]]. The position was created on 23 April 1988, when Luxembourg was promoted from a bishopric. The seat of the [[Archiepiscopal see|see]] is [[Notre-Dame Cathedral, Luxembourg|Notre-Dame Cathedral]], in [[Luxembourg City]].
