{{refimprove|date=October 2012}} [[File:Sagar Shiv Mandir 1.jpg|thumb|Sagar Shiv Mandir]] [[File:2007-09-09 Mauritius 10.jpg|thumb|Sagar Shiv Mandir]] '''Sagar Shiv Mandir''' is a [[Hindu temple]] sitting on the island of Goyave de Chine, Poste de Flacq, [[Mauritius]]. Sagar Shiv Mandir is on the eastern part of Mauritius. It is a place of worship for Hindus settled in Mauritius and it is also visited by tourists.<ref name="">{{cite web |first= |last= |title=Hindu temples across the world |url=http://www.hinduonline.co/HinduCulture/ListOfTemplesWorldwide.html |publisher= |location= |date= |archivedate= |accessdate=10 October 2012 }}</ref> The temple was constructed in 2007 and it hosts a 108 feet height bronze coloured statue of [[Shiva]].{{citation needed|date=October 2012}}
The temple is similar to the [[Temple in the Sea]] in [[Trinidad and Tobago]].
